NFL Commissioner Goodell Arrives for Talks as Expiration of Contract Nears

-- B y   A a r o n   K u r i l o f f
-- 
2011-03-03T14:19:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/nfl-commissioner-goodell-arrives-for-talks-as-expiration-of-contract-nears.html
National Football League
Commissioner Roger Goodell led a group of league leaders today
into the site of negotiations with the players union, with
scheduled expiration of the current contract 15 hours away.  Goodell, lawyers Eric Grubman and Bob Batterman, New York
Giants President John Mara and others entered the offices of the
Federal Mediation and Conciliation Service in  Washington  just
before 9 a.m. local time.  The collective bargaining agreement with the NFL Players
Association is set to run out at one second before midnight.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  